description.narrative: UNICEF significantly contributed to enhance the service delivery by strengthening the community health system. In 2019, about 750,000 children under five were treated for common childhood illnesses. With UNICEF technical and financial assistance, the Health Sector Reform was effectively engaged. In the six regions supported by UNICEF, the number of primary Health Care facilities providing clinical care to children under five using the Integrated Management of Neonatal and Childhood Illness (IMNCI) approach increased from 162 in 2017 to 547 in 2019. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
